messages.text:
How do apply the *same dispatch pattern to multiple methods*? In this example I am avoiding having to define methods for `f`  and `g` individually by awkwardly sub-typing `Function` . This leads to method overwrite warnings when I put this into my module.
```struct Integrand &lt;: Function end

const f = Integrand()
function f( x::T ) where T&lt;:Number
	return x^2 - x
end

const g = Integrand() 
function g( x::T ) where T&lt;:Number
	return - log(x) + sin(x)
end

# this method applies to both f and g
function (integrand::Integrand)( X::AbstractVector; dx=0.01 )
	return sum( x -&gt; integrand(x)*dx, X )
end```
What is the recommended way to do this?

